com.google.code.siren4j.component.builder
Class EntityBuilder

java.lang.Object
  com.google.code.siren4j.component.builder.BaseBuilder<Entity>
      com.google.code.siren4j.component.builder.EntityBuilder

public class EntityBuilder
extends BaseBuilder<Entity>

The EntityBuilder allows the construction of an Entity object via a fluent builder API. 

 Example Usage:
 
 EntityBuilder builder = EntityBuilder.newInstance();
 Entity result = builder
    .setEntityClass("test")
    .addProperty("foo", "hello")
    .addProperty("number", 1)
    .addLinks(getLinks())
    .addActions(getActions())
    .build();

setHref

public EntityBuilder setHref(String href)
Set the href of the entity to be built. This method can be called many times but only the value of the last call is used in the built entity. This is a required property if this entity is an embedded link, as specified by the Siren specification. If set then this entity will be considered an embedded link.

postProcess

protected void postProcess(Entity obj)
Description copied from class: BaseBuilder
A subclass can post process the component instance after built by the base but before it is returned by BaseBuilder.build(). Commonly used if the builder is adding something to the component as it will typically maintain the list itself and then add the values in BaseBuilder.postProcess(Object).

Overrides:
postProcess in class BaseBuilder<Entity>
Parameters:
